deck: Director Pandora Peters is the head of W.A.N.D. - S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Wizardry Alchemy Necromancy Division - which handles supernatural threats.
description:
Origin

Creation

Pandora Peters was created by writers Ben Acker and Ben Blacker, and artist Matteo Lolli. She first appeared in 2014's Thunderbolts Annual #1.

Major Story Arcs

Thunderbolts

When it appeared that Doctor Strange was slowly enslaving the world into a mindless state of magical happiness, Thunderbolt Ross mobilized his team of Thunderbolts to take the Sorcerer Supreme out. To do this, the Thunderbolts needed to arm themselves with magical items to match Strange's might. While the Thunderbolts were successful in acquiring certain items, W.A.N.D. wound up helping them more than they would ever know. Taken to W.A.N.D. headquarters with a magical spell, Ross and the Leader met Director Pandora Peters and her right hand, Todd. The two Thunderbolts were magically restrained to prevent them from causing trouble, but were also given free rein of W.A.N.D.'s stores of magical weaponry and artifacts. After getting what they needed, Peters had Todd wipe the Thunderbolts' memory of their meeting, and replaced it with a memory of them getting their artifacts from a magical cache of Doctor Druid.

The Thunderbolts eventually proved victorious against the mad Doctor Strange, except that he turned out to actually be Oberoth'm'gozz in disguise, the True King of Faeries who sought to conquer Earth with his legion of Old Ones. Peters and her agents of W.A.N.D. soon arrived after the king's defeat to clean up the magical mess he'd left, and to bring back the real Doctor Strange. Peters reintroduced herself to the Thunderbolts and apologized for not handling the situation themselves, as they didn't know it wasn't actually Doctor Strange who was the threat. Afterwards though she had Todd wipe their memories once again, making them forget about their battle with Oberoth'm'gozz and replaced it with one of the Thunderbolts having a nice lunch of shawarma together.

Powers & Abilities

As director of W.A.N.D., Pandora Peters has access to numerous magical resources. With W.A.N.D. spell casters to support her, she can even control other people by ordering them around with the words, "Simon says." She is covered in numerous tattoos - most likely of a magical nature, and also carries a wand with her at all times that she is most likely well versed in using.
name: Pandora Peters

deck: Captain Alcohol is a comic book superhero created by the Canadian government to discourage drinking alcohol.
description:
History

Al Cohol was an alien from the planet Barkelda. According to Al, it is an utopia except their lack of alcohol control. Al accidentally created a fire, which killed his family. To forget his woes, he volunteered to a mission in space. However, he crashed on Earth. He was somehow frozen. An Inuit man, Kirnik, found them before Al broke free. After explaining his back story to Kirnik, Kirnik's town was attacked by Ravenmen. The duo managed to escape, but not defeat them. Captain Al ended up defeating a drunk Inuit man and gave a hypocritical anti-alcohol speech. Al fell in love with Lois Alley (a Lois Lane-stand in), who was captured by the villain Billy Vermin. Despite Al's attempt to save her, the Royal Canadian Mounted Police saved the day. Al became upset and got drunk. Lois was killed rampaging muskoxen. Al got even more drunk. He finally managed to defeat a villain in the form of Firey Fritz (Al's father, who transforms into a monster when he drinks alcohol).

Powers and Abilities

Al Cohol's powers are poorly defined. He manages to break out of ice (which would require super strength and invulnerability), but otherwise seems to act like a normal human.
name: Captain Alcohol

deck: Queen of the Golden Realm and leader of the Golden Guardians.
description:
Origin

Sha Lux is the leader and ruler of the Golden Realm and the Golden Guardians. The worlds of magic have realties overlapping. There are places such as the Void realm, a place of darkness and hopelessness where many dangerous magic users have been exiled. Then there are places like the Golden realm, a realm where magic exists in great quantity, physics bend, order is enforced. Sha Lux commands the enforcers of the Golden realm. When the powerful Serke seeks to claim Earth, its up to druid Sudana, Hank Medley, Sparkles and the powerful Kon to oppose him. Serke focusing on eliminating Kon himself leaves his followers Torgan, Alle and Hector to track down Sudana and Hank. Escaping to the Golden realm, Sudana is familiar with the ream and hesitant to turn to Sha Lux and the group avoid rousing her attention.

Creation

Sha Lux is a Aspen MLT character created by Vince Hernandez and Vincenzo Cucca for the second volume of Charismagic. Sha Lux first appears in Charismagic #4 - The Golden Law.

Character Evolution

Sha Lax appears in a limited role, mainly as a neutral supporting character. The character has a history with Sudana and appears quite important within the Charismagic universe.

Major Story Arcs

The Golden Law

When Las Vegas stage magician Hank Medley, druid Sudana and cat Sparkles need to seek refuge from Torgan, Alle and Hector they travel to the Golden realm which is under the jurisdiction of Sha Lax. Outnumbered by the Golden Guardians, the group must travel to and met with the ruler of the land Sha Lux. Sha Lux's mannerisms and descent clad in decorative armor make for an impressive site, causing Hank to sigh whilst annoying Sudana simultaneously. Unfortunately Sha Lux is more concerned about the presence of the cat Sparkles than the impending threat of Serke. This proves to be a mistake as her throne room is attacked by Torgan, Alle and Hector and a host of creatures summoned by Alle.

War of the Worlds

The mighty lion like entity Torgan had smashed through the Golden realm palace and Sha Lux had been knocked down. A fight would break out between her Golden Guardians, Sudana, Hank and Sparkles and the invading Torgan Alle and Hector with a swarm of dark creatures summoned by Alle. Sha Lux bearing a strong hatred for cat like creatures and having also previously defeated Torgan would attempt to freeze the energy beast in the air enraged after it had killed her Guardians. Despite such a tactic having worked in the past, Torgan being more powerful now could resist and would charge towards Sha Lux looking for revenge until the druid Sudana would step in and with her assistance Sha Lux was able to defeat Torgan once again.

Powers and Abilities

Sha Lux is very powerful in her realm. Its very laws can be manipulated and adjusted by Sha Lux and her magic and as such her abilities and power can be manifested in a variety of ways, including gravity control, temperature control, durability, energy manipulation and generation and likely plenty more.
name: Sha Lux

deck: A giant powerful magical lion like creature. Serves the powerful Serke.

Origin

Torgan is a mighty magical entity that appears as a Lion made of green flame and energy. Torgan is summoned from slumber by a possessed Alle and Hector, all three to serve under the powerful Serke. Despite having a heavy disdain for humans, Torgan being a magical entity, Torgan's loyalty and subservience to Serke override that particular dislike. One of Torgan's first objectives after being awoken is to hunt and stop Hank Medley from gaining an artifact that will allow him and his group to reach the Golden Realm.

Creation

Torgan is an Aspen MLT character first appearing in Charismagic #2 - The Illusion of Power. The character is created by Vince Hernandez.

Character Evolution

Torgan appears as an antagonist in the second volume of the hit series Charismagic.

Major Story Arcs

deck: The Hate-Monger was created by Psycho-Man and sent to Earth to help destroy the Fantastic Four.
description:
Origin

The Hate-Monger was a construct created by Psycho-Man who spread words of hate at various rallies across New York City, shape-shifting to appropriate forms when necessary.

Creation

Hate-Monger was created by John Byrne and first appeared in Fantastic Four #279.

Character Evolution

Psycho-Man's construct is the third super-villain to name themselves Hate-Monger, after a subsequent Adolf Hitler clone and Man-Beast, and is the second Hate-Monger to fight the Fantastic Four. This version of Hate-Monger has no connection to the previous two, except in similar powerset. Psycho-Man's Hate-Monger also appeared in the crossover Secret Wars II and was killed as part of the Scourge crossover. Since the construct's death, Animus became the next person to assume the Hate-Monger identity before the original Hate-Monger returned. This Hate-Monger received an Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe entry in Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe A-Z #5.

Powers and Abilities

Hate-Monger is a shape-shifter with the ability to instill hatred into those who hear his voice or come into physical contact with him.

description:
Comics

WWE Superstars (Super Genius Comics)

Seth Rollins is a cop in Titan City.

Wrestling career

Colby Lopez is the real name of professional wrestler Seth Rollins. He is a Davenport, Iowa native.

Indie Career

Before his contract with World Wrestling Entertainment, Lopez has enjoyed success as a professional wrestler in several independent/non-televised promotions, including AIW (Absolute Intense Wrestling), All American Wrestling, Full Impact Pro (FIP), Independent Wrestling Association- Mid-South (IWA-Mid-South), Mr. Chainsaw Productions Wrestling, and NWA Midwest. In Pro Wrestling Guerrilla and Ring of Honor (RoH), Lopez partnered with Jimmy Jacobs, holding tag team titles with him in both organizations. As Tyler Black, Lopez was a member of Jacobs' faction, the Fall.

WWE

After success in the WWE's new developmental territory, NXT (the former Florida Championship Wrestling), Lopez debuted on WWE television as Seth Rollins alongside fellow NXT alumni, Roman Reigns and Dean Ambrose as "the Shield." Clad in police riot gear, the so-called "Hounds of Justice," were booked as heels, initially allied with then-heel CM Punk and then the Authority. With Reigns, Seth Rollins won the WWE Tag Team titles, but they lost the belts in a match to the Brotherhood after interference by the Big Show. The Shield also won three Slammy Awards in 2013 for Faction of the Year, for Breakout Star(s) of the Year, and for Trending Now (Hashtag) of the Year [#BelieveInTheShield].

Feud with Evolution and Treachery

As Rollins, Lopez and the other members of the Shield have been booked against opponents under the pretense of enforcing the Authority's will. Despite being pushed as heels, the trio gained an overwhelming amount of fan support. This led to the decision to gradually transition them into babyfaces. After a short feud with "Corporate Kane," who more closely represented the interests of the Authority (Triple H and his wife, Stephanie McMahon), the Shield turned on Triple H. To match the trio in number, Triple H reformed Evolution with Randy Orton and Batista; former Evolution member Ric Flair retired from the WWE, but made a rare appearance as a non-wrestler, voicing support for the Shield over his own former faction. Rollins and the Shield were booked with two PPV wins over Evolution in six-man matches at Extreme Rules, and the following month at Payback.

On the June 2, 2014 episode of Raw, Batista apparently left Evolution. Roman Reigns and Randy Orton were to compete against one another, but Rollins betrayed the Shield, attacking both Ambrose and Reigns from behind with a chair and then standing over their prone bodies with Orton and Triple H. A week later, he revealed in an interview with Michael Cole that he was the architect of the Shield, and that he felt like he was severing a business relationship with partners in order to evolve, rather than betraying the bonds of fellowship. At the Money in the Bank pay-per-view event, Rollins became the number one contender for the WWE World Heavyweight Championship titles with assistance from Kane. The next night on Raw, Dean Ambrose vowed to thwart all of Rollins attempts to cash in his championship opportunity, and did just that when it appeared as though Rollins might capitalize on a seemingly down and out champion, John Cena.

deck: Three-time WWE Divas champion, married to CM Punk.
description:
Biography

27-year old April Jeanette Brooks is a female professional wrestler of Puerto Rican descent currently employed by World Wrestling Entertainment as AJ Lee. Previously, she wrestled for Women Superstars Uncensored (WSU), where she held the WSU Tag Team title alongside her then-partner, Brooke Carter (Brittney Savage). Her current in-ring gimmick is that of a loner who cares about the. Divas Championship more than any person. AJ Lee has stated in interviews she is a comic book fan, citing Harley Quinn as pivotal to her in-ring persona. She told interviewer Craig Tello that the X-Men and the Fantastic Four, as well as Spider-Man are among her favorite comics. She is also a video game fan, and the first female winner or the WWE's Superstar Challenge at 2012's Wrestlemania XXVIII Axxess.

Lee is a former 2 time WWE Diva of the Year and Pro Wrestling Illustrated's Woman of the Year for three consecutive years, 2012-2014. She's the only woman in history to win PWI woman of the year 3 consecutive years. Lee has the longest single reign as WWE Diva's champion at 295 days, and the most combined days as champion at 406. After appearing at Wrestlemania XXX, where she defeated 13 other WWE Divas in the Vickie Guerrero Invitational, AJ Lee lost her belt to the debuting Paige the next night on Raw. On the June 30, 2014 episode of Raw, Lee returned and defeated Paige to reclaim her belt. She lost the belt to Paige again, and then won it back a month later.

In her personal life, Mendez was formerly romantically linked to her trainer, Ring of Honor (RoH) wrestler Jay Lethal (more popularly known as Total Nonstop Action's [TNA] Black Machismo). On June 13, 2014, she married fellow WWE roster member, CM Punk. Rumors that Mendez is pregnant with CM Punk's child are erroneous.

In Comics

AJ Lee currently appears in the WWE Superstars comic, written by prolific professional wrestler Mick Foley and published by Super Genius. She appears in the background of the first issue's variant cover with CM Punk in an homage to the classic Jack Kirby cover of Fantastic Four #51 - This Man...This Monster.

Other Media

AJ Lee is also a voice actress in Scooby Doo & The Wrestlemania Mystery (2014).
